From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 21 Jul 2026 12:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] rockchip: rk3576-generic: enable the util command set

The rk3576-util image is a recovery and bring-up tool driven at the
prompt. Add the commands that job needs beyond a booting image:

  * bootmenu  -- an interactive menu on the muxed console (serial +
    HDMI), so an operator with a dead OS picks a boot target with the
    keyboard instead of typing.
  * clk       -- `clk dump` reads the live clock tree; the RK3576
    bring-up turned on the CPU/DDR/USB PLLs and the CNTPCT source, and
    this is how their rates are confirmed on the board.
  * memtest   -- a DRAM walk from the prompt before trusting a board.
  * md5sum,
    sha1sum   -- hash a rescue image loaded over USB or the network
    before it is written to storage.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
index b0466e3c..c1a7f0d2 100644
--- a/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
+++ b/configs/generic-rk3576_defconfig
@@ -70,3 +70,8 @@ CONFIG_ERRNO_STR=y
 # CONFIG_CMD_CLS is not set
 CONFIG_CMD_SMC=y
 CONFIG_CMD_CACHE=y
+CONFIG_CMD_BOOTMENU=y
+CONFIG_CMD_CLK=y
+CONFIG_CMD_MEMTEST=y
+CONFIG_CMD_MD5SUM=y
+CONFIG_CMD_SHA1SUM=y
